Eskom is investigating a fire that broke out at the Kusile Power Station near Witbank, Mpumalanga on Friday (10 August). No injuries have been reported. Eskom confirmed this in a statement. “Eskom confirms that a fire that started at the Kusile Power Station Unit 3 fabric filter plant between 17:30 and 18:30,” the power utility said. “The fire was immediately extinguished by the power station’s Fire Team.“The incident is under investigation.” 